 \"rank\": 1.4903583149842185e-07, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a home Olympics\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1586}, {\"ngram\": \"four years\", \"from\": 1605, \"to\": 1615}, {\"ngram\": \"her mind\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1630}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And in a passing of the baton moment, Canada's Summer McIntosh enhanced her status as the rising star of women's swimming by winning her third gold medal of the games in the 200-metre individual medley.\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1671, \"end\": 1677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.95351574966391, \"rank\": 0.04720583104356396, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1680, \"end\": 1695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a passing\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1649}, {\"ngram\": \"the baton moment\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1669}, {\"ngram\": \"her status\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1715}, {\"ngram\": \"the rising star\", \"from\": 1719, \"to\": 1734}, {\"ngram\": \"women's swimming\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1754}, {\"ngram\": \"her third gold medal\", \"from\": 1766, \"to\": 1786}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1799}, {\"ngram\": \"the 200-metre individual medley\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1834}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 17-year-old produced a brilliant late surge to win in a time of 2min 06.56sec, the third-fastest time in history.\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 1954, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a brilliant late surge\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1884}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 1895, \"to\": 1901}, {\"ngram\": \"2min 06.56sec\", \"from\": 1905, \"to\": 1918}, {\"ngram\": \"the third-fastest time\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 1942}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 1953}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kate Douglass of the USA finished second to take silver while Australian Kaylee McKeown took the bronze after American Alex Walsh, who had finished third, was disqualified.\", \"from\": 1956, \"to\": 2128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1956, \"end\": 1969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}, {\"begin\": 2018, \"end\": 2028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999794825898158, \"rank\": 1.6787190667074184e-05, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 2066, \"end\": 2074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999665034691584, \"rank\": 3.3392032093669974e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2075, \"end\": 2085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the USA\", \"from\": 1973, \"to\": 1980}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2011}, {\"ngram\": \"the bronze\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2059}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh had already claimed gold in the 400-metre individual medley and the 200-metre butterfly, as well as a silver in the 400-metre freestyle.\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2275, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2130, \"end\": 2138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.128431672774589e-14, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2159, \"to\": 2163}, {\"ngram\": \"the 400-metre individual medley\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2198}, {\"ngram\": \"the 200-metre butterfly\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2226}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver\", \"from\": 2239, \"to\": 2247}, {\"ngram\": \"the 400-metre freestyle\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2274}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's pretty surreal.\", \"from\": 2277, \"to\": 2298, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am just so proud of myself, how I have been able to recover and manage the events because it is a lot,\\\" said the teenager, who also won silver in the 400-metre freestyle during what has been an intense games for her.\", \"from\": 2299, \"to\": 2517, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the events\", \"from\": 2372, \"to\": 2382}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 2397, \"to\": 2402}, {\"ngram\": \"the teenager\", \"from\": 2410, \"to\": 2422}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2443}, {\"ngram\": \"the 400-metre freestyle\", \"from\": 2447, \"to\": 2470}, {\"ngram\": \"an intense games\", \"from\": 2492, \"to\": 2508}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The reason I am able to do this j